----------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Model structurally captures admin action logging with safety invariants and post-state reachability.
-- Summary 2: Fixed type errors: replaced 'Admin' (Permission) with 'Admin_Team' (Actor) in predicates and assertions.
-- Summary 3: Fixed type error in tc_log02_holds by removing incorrect target condition (Actor used as Resource).
-- Summary 4: Facts enforce exactly two channels per operation (latency <=2, availability >=2), consistent with two defined interfaces.
-- Assumption 1: Admin_Team and Audit_Committee are the only actor roles; Admin_Team represents admin users.
-- Assumption 2: Write permission models typical action (ban/warn).
-- Assumption 3: Post1 and Post2 abstractly represent logged and error states respectively.
-- Assumption 4: Target resource set includes Audit_Log_Database as proxy for log entry.
-- Assumption 5: Interfaces Admin_Action_API and Audit_Log_Database are the only channels used.
-- Open issue 1: Log entry details (admin ID, action type, timestamp, target user) are not explicitly modeled; they are approximated by state and resource inclusion.
-- Open issue 2: The concurrent NFR assertion (nfr_assert_scalability_concurrency) may be unsatisfiable due to facts enforcing exactly two channels and bounded scope.
-- Open issue 3: The model does not represent high-volume concurrent actions or 100ms performance constraints.


